### [Jeremiah Chapter 32](../../../bib/kjv/jer032.htm#001.md)

[Jeremiah](../../../bib/kjv/jer001.htm#001.md)

<span class="margnote"><span id="an_000">jer 32:0</span></span>

Overview

[Jer 32:1](../../../bib/kjv/jer032.htm#001.md), Jeremiah, being imprisoned
by Zedekiah for his prophecy, [Jer
32:6](../../../bib/kjv/jer032.htm#006.md), buys Hanameel's field; [Jer
32:13](../../../bib/kjv/jer032.htm#013.md), Baruch must preserve the
evidences, as tokens of the people's return; v.16, Jeremiah in his
prayer complains to God; v.26, God confirms the captivity for their
sins; v.36, and promises a gracious return.

